name: The Hellfire Hunt, Part 5: Beyond Belief
Wiser Times

description:
1. Wraparound cover by Jim Aparo.
  2. Splash page by Jose Delbo and Joe Orlando.
  3. "The Innocent Who Hated!" (Superman and Batman) written by Denny O'Neill, penciled by Dick Dillin, inked by Frank McLaughlin, colored by Gene D'Angelo and lettered by Ben Oda.
  4. "Death Ransom!" (Black Lightning) written by Denny O'Neill, penciled by George Tuska, inked by Bob Smith, colored by Jerry Serpe and lettered by Shelly Leferman.
  5. "Time Keeps on Killing" (Green Arrow and Clock King) written by Paul Kupperberg, penciled by Jose Delbo, inked by Frank McLaughlin, colored by Jerry Serpe and lettered by Shelly Leferman.
  6. "Attack of the In-and-Out Invaders" (Hawkman and Hawkgirl) written by Gerry Conway, penciled by Rich Buckler, inked by Romeo Tanghal, colored by Adrienne Roy and lettered by Ben Oda.
  7. "The Invincible Man" (Captain Marvel and Invincible Man (i.e. Mr. Mind)) written by E. Nelson Bridwell, penciled by Don Newton, inked by Kurt Schaffenberger, colored by Adrienne Roy and lettered by Albert De Guzman.

Notes:

  • 64 pages with no ads.
  • Doorknob-type Stopper Arrow, Boxing Glove Arrow?, Smoke Arrow? and Bola Arrow (flashback) used.
  • Roy Harper cameo flashback from World's Finest Comics #111.
  • Clock Repairman's company is named Levitz Clocks which is a homage to Paul Levitz in the Green Arrow story.
  • The book Collected Papers of Todd Klein is a homage to Todd Klein in the Captain Marvel story.
name: The Innocent Who Hated! / Death Ransom! / Time Keeps on Killing / Attack of the In-and-Out Invaders / The Invincible Man

description:
Seeking to kidnap Psylocke, Kuragari dispatched his Undercloaks to bring her to his realm, but she and Archangel prove too much for the Undercloaks, and they fail in their mission.  During the battle, the Undercloaks drop a ring which Kuragari intended for Psylocke.  Though she knows the ring to be a symbol of evil, she places it on her finger, confident that the ring might lead her to the source of her recent personality transformation. 
Meanwhile, Gomurr arrives seeking to enlist the aid of Psylocke and Archangel against invasion by Kuragari.  He is aghast to see that Psylocke wears the ring.  Moments later, Kuragari arrives, defeats Gomurr and Warren, wounding him, and then kidnaps Betsy.
name: When the Devil Comes a Calling

description:
While Archangel and Gomurr recover from their fight with Kuragari, Psylocke awakens in a palace in the Crimson Dawn, captive to Kuragari.  She tries to attack him, but neither her martial arts expertise, nor her psychic weapons have any effect on him.  Kuragari bests her in battle, then assigns his Undercloaks to transform Psylocke into one of them. 
Telling Warren that only by entering the Crimson Dawn and saving Betsy can the world be saved, Gomurr teleports the X-Man to the other dimension, where he is confronted by a transformed Psylocke.
name: The Dark Side!
The Dawning Dusk

description:
Superman and Batman - longtime allies - are at odds when confronted with a crisis. Earth has been secretly overrun by two races from beyond the stars. One race uses everything in its path to assure its propagation and survival, the other is a culture of hunters, bound to a strict code that reduces every encounter with outsiders to a battle against becoming their prey.

The Man of Steel and The Dark Knight are Earths first line of defense. But they cannot agree how to deal with the Aliens and the Predators. For, as ruthless as these creatures are, Superman feels that all life is sacred and must be protected, while Batman cares about protecting humanity above all.

But their hand may be forced by an outside agency dedicated to the extermination of all interplanetary intruders, and all who are seen to protect and abet them. And that may include our heroes!
name: Book Two Of Two

volume.name: Superman and Batman vs. Aliens and Predators

description:
Overview

They've hunted the Dark Knight Detective. They've gone after the Man of Steel. Now they're prepared to go after the most challenging prey imaginable: the entire Justice League of America. The World's Greatest Super-Heroes go up against the galaxy's deadliest hunters in JLA vs. Predator. When a group of Predators arrive on Earth, they make targets of each of the JLA members -- relishing in the thrill of the hunt. They engage in the ultimate sport of attempting to kill the most powerful heroes ever known. But how can any foes, even ones as relentless as the Predators, possibly beat our heroes? Because this time, the Predators are equipped with the incredible powers of the Justice League itself! With the help of a rogue Dominion geneticist, the aliens have transformed themselves into "Meta-Predators" -- super-powered versions of the same ultimate hunters who stalk the universe's most dangerous game! Can even the mighty JLA withstand the savage onslaught of a squad of Predators with Superman's strength, the Flash's speed, and Plastic Man's morphing powers?

Just another typical night of insanity for Mary Jane as she deals with an obsessed stalker and with watching helplessly while Spider-Man slugs it out with...Iron Man? And that' s just a warm-up for the devastating confrontation she has with Peter that results in the last thing she expected to hear.
name: The Other - Evolve Or Die, Part 2 of 12: Denial

description:
Overview

Having finally accepted his fate, Peter Parker decides to put the red and blue tights in the closet and spend some quality time with Aunt May and MJ. But Morlun's got other plans...
name: The Other - Evolve Or Die, Part 5 of 12: Retreat
Awesome Arachnid Action Packed First Issue

description: A dark and frightening fully painted novella, MR. PUNCH tells the tale of a young boy's loss of innocence results from a horrific confrontation with his past. Spending a summer at his grandfather's seaside arcade, a troubled adolescent harmlessly becomes involved with a mysterious Punch and Judy Man and a mermaid-portraying woman. But when the violent puppet show triggers buried memories of the boy's family, the lives of all become feverishly intertwined. With disturbing mysteries and half-truths uncontrollably unraveling, the young boy is forced to deal with his family's dark secrets of violence, betrayal, and guilt.
name: The Comical Tragedy or Tragical Comedy of Mr. Punch

volume.name: The Comical Tragedy or Tragical Comedy of Mr. Punch

description: Includes material reprinted from: Friendly Neighborhood Spider-Man #1, Spider-Man/Red Sonja #3 and The Amazing Spider-Man #249.

"THE OTHER: EVOLVE OR DIE" PART 8 (OF 12) THE SPIDER-MAN CROSSOVER EVENT OF THE DECADE CONTINUES HERE! Beaten to the edge of death, hovering in a place short of heaven or hell, Spidey is about to embark on a journey unlike anything he's ever experienced. If he's going to have any hope to thwart Morlun's obscene mission, then he's got two choices: Evolve or die...
name: The Other - Evolve Or Die, Part 8 of 12: Aftermath

description:
Overview

THE SPIDER-MAN CROSSOVER EVENT OF THE DECADE ENDS HERE!

The fourth and final month of “The Other,” a startling super-story spanning four months that has turned the wall-crawler’s world upside down, and set the stage for the year to come, uniting the creative talents behind all three Spider-Man titles! With great power must come great responsibility...but what comes with great understanding? In the past few months, Peter Parker has traveled to places he never has before. Now the question is, can he go home?
name: The Other - Evolve Or Die, Part 11 of 12: Destiny's Child

description: Collects all 6 issues.
name: TPB

description: Jump ahead 20-30 years. The Cube has virtually complete control over all software in the world. The Internet pervades all aspects of life, from running electricity to running your toaster. CEO Maxwell Minsky has a new incredibly powerful platform about to be launched that can grow organically with your needs, but that will know absolutely everything about you. Turner, part of an underground of hackers, still believes in freeware, and ID had his memory wiped out. As Turner and his group help him regain some of his memory, he realizes he was prominent at the Cube and what he was designing was incredibly dangerous. Already, random acts of sudden destruction are being recorded worldwide. Yet, strangely, someone keeps sending a female cyborg to ID's rescue... A fascinating world that could very well be our own. See if anything can be done to prevent it!
name: The 3rd Degree

description: The first volume of one of Japan's longest running manga series is now back in print in an English-language edition, reformatted to match the current 3x3 Eyes titles. From a hidden land in the Tibetan Highlands comes Pai, a strange and beautiful woman come to Tokyo to find a young man named Yakumo who can help her in her quest...to become human! When Pai finally finds her man, the two set off in search of an artifact that can transform her, but it will take all her mystic powers to keep the reckless Yakumo alive - even if she has to steal his soul to protect him!
name: House of Demons
Mickey Mouse outwits the Phantom Blot

description:
1. The Echo Valley (Donald, Daisy)

2. Malayalaya (Donald, Huey, Dewey, Louie, Uncle Scrooge)

3. Donald Buys a TV Set ((Donald, Huey, Dewey, Louie, Daisy)

4. Brush Salesman (Donald, Huey, Dewey, Louie)

description:
Overview

The end of Spawn. 'Nuff said.

After bathing in the blood of the virgins, the demonic Morana assumes the mantle of the Spawn. Cyan must see farther into the future than she ever has before, if she hopes to save the lives of her parents – and the future of the human race.
name: Bad Blood

description:
Overview

The most stunning revelation ever seen in the pages of Spawn! Behind the scenes of human history, one man has been pulling the strings. Now at last, Mammon's plans come to deadly fruition.

The revelations come thick and fast as Nyx becomes the unwilling host for Spawn's costume. Mammon finally reveals his true purpose, and we learn the horrifying secret of Morana's true identity. There will be blood!
name: Transformations
The Blood of Dr. Necrosis
Skin Deep The Conclusion
New Era, New Adventure, New Avengers Begins

description: Brainwave, Athena, Bulldog and Virtuoso are THE OLYMPIANS - Britain's national superteam...and Britain's national joke. Can Max Tarrant, their new administrator, keep them teammates from killing each other long enough to turn around their disastrous media image? Not likely!
name: It's Not The End Of The World

description:
The second volume of one of Japan's longest running manga series is now back in print in an English-language edition, reformatted to match the current 3x3 Eyes titles. Yakumo is an ordinary Tokyo high-school student who is helping a not-so-ordinary 300-year-old girl from Tibet named Pai on a quest to discover a way for Pai to become human, a quest that exposes Yakumo to the terrors best kept in nightmares . But when Yakumo returns to Japan thinking he can resume his old life, he discovers that the evils of hell have come with him!

Collects issues 1-5.
name: Curse of the Gesu

description: The collected editions of the manga horror/action epic finally continue! From a hidden world in the Tibetan highlands comes Pai, a strange and beautiful girl with a difference: three eyes and three hundred birthdays behind her! Sent to Tokyo by a dying anthropologist, Pai must find his son, Yakumo, to help her in her quest... to become human! But when Pai merges Yakumo's soul with that of her immortal supernatural familiar to save his life, the urgency of their mission becomes even greater as Yakumo fights to reclaim his own humanity. Pai and Yakumo discover the existence of a statue that may help end their quest, but to obtain it they'll have to take on the dwellers in the dark, who need the statue to revive a dread demonic lord and bring about an inhuman kingdom of immortal evil!
name: Flight of the Demon

description: Everything changes in this volume of 3x3 Eyes, one of Japan's most popular and longest-running series! The zombie teenager Yakumo has been searching for Pai, the girl he loves, for years. When he finds her, she's in big trouble! The amnesiac Pai has forgotten all about her inhuman heritage and mystical powers, and an evil group of supernatural Puppet People are on the hunt for her! Can Yakumo use his new special attack moves to rescue Pai and restore her memories? Or will she run from him -- and the truth -- as well?
name: Blood of the Sacred Demon

description: After living as a human with no recollection of her three-hundred plus years in a mystical Tibetan kingdom, Pai's supernatural powers have returned, but not her memories. These wondrous abilities are an exciting development for a seemingly typical Tokyo teenager...until she discovers that her Sanjiyan, the monstrous source of her power, is on the loose and can only be controlled within her by the Claw of Shiva, a sorcerous artifact that the memory-challenged Pai just happens to have bagged and tossed into the trash! But Yakumo, Pai's mortal-made-immortal boyfriend, is at her side, which for him may not be a good thing. He may be immortal but he's not indestructible, and eternal life isn't much comfort when you're being torn to pieces!
name: Summoning the Beast

description: Pai, the beautiful 300-year-old amnesiac mystic, and her companion-cum-immortal slave, Tokyo student Yakumo Fujii, search China for ancient relics to provide clues to the location of Pai's hidden Tibetan homeland, where Pai's memories can be restored. But the two are not the only ones in search of these objects. Both the dashing relic-hunter Jake McDonald and the nefarious Choukai, are trying to get their mitts on a certain mystic incense burner. And when Choukai traps Pai within a sorcerous binding circle, Yakumo is torn by the fateful decision of whether or not to pay the artifact as ransom to free Pai and by doing so, dooming Pai's memories and his own chance of returning to his mortal existence.
name: Key to the Sacred Land

description: Pai, the beautiful 300-year-old amnesiac mystic, and her companion-cum-immortal slave, Tokyo student Yakumo Fujii, may have found the clues they seek to help them discover the secrets of the Sacred Land. Joined by the dashing relic-hunter, Jake MacDonald, Yakumo and Pai discover an ancient temple that may hold the key to returning Pai and Yakumo to their human forms. However their journey of exploration becomes a fight for survival as the pair are once again pitted against the evil forces of Kaiyan Wang.
name: The Shadow of the Kunlun

description: Pai doesn’t look a day over sixteen; of course, she’s 300 years old and the last of an ancient mystical race. Yakumo looks no different than your average Tokyo teen; however, he’s been resurrected from the dead as Pai’s immortal slave and defender. They’re both on a quest to return Pai to her hidden homeland and ultimately to return Yakumo to his mortal form. They’ve been through hell and high water to find a lost Tibetan shrine that holds the keys to the Sacred Land of Kunlun. But with the mission accomplished, the return to Kunlun turns out not to be the heartfelt reunion Pai had hoped for, but could instead reveal her incredible journey to be only a ruse that could well release the evil Kaiyan Wang from imprisonment in the Sacred Land! Collecting stories from Super Manga Blast! issues #32-40.
name: Descent of the Mystic City

description:
One day Yakumo, a high-school student in Tokyo, met a girl named Pai. Pai was not human. She was Sanziyan-unkara, an immortal being with mysterious powers. Yakumo promised that he would find a way to make Pai human. Together, they set out to Hong Kong on a great adventure that was to begin a modern legend!

Now, the adventures of Pai and Yakumo continue!Yakumo returns to Japan believing that he can resume his old life as a high-school student, an existence he had left behind -- ignoring Pai's warning that to do so will subject everyone he knows to the evils of hell itself.
name: Chapter 1

description: His apartment has been trashed; he's had a run-in with the police; his friends treat him like a monster from hell itself; and now, on top of it all, Yakumo finds himself attacked by a mysterious creature in a trench coat. How'd the life of an ordinary high-school student fall into such disrepair? Why not ask Pai, his new three-eyed, immortal friend!
name: Chapter 2

description: Yakuma's ordinary life ended the day he met Pai, an immortal being with a desperate wish to become human. They've been through a lot together -- some bad, much good, all extraordinary -- and have tried to assimilate it into a normal life. Now Yakuma has come to accept that normalcy is a thing of his past, and so he and Pai prepare to leave Tokyo forever. But before they get out of town, they face the strangest occurrence yet; the appearance of the deadly mythical creature -- the dreaded Gesu!
name: Chapter 3

description: Yakumo is an ordinary high-school student whose life has been turned upside-down by a three-eyed girl. She is Pai, an immortal with strange powers and a talent for drawing trouble into her path, such as the monstrous creature called the Gesu. Can Yakumo and his friend Natsuko survive the Gesu's attack? Only if Pai's immortal powers are up to the job. . .
name: Chapter 4

description: Yakumo died -- and his life will never be the same again. He's become a zombie, courtesy of his newly found friend Pai, herself an immortal being with strange powers and a talent for attracting trouble. His only course seems to be to leave Japan -- and his old life -- behind forever. But when the marauding monster called the Gesu attacks, he's got to stand his ground and defend Pai. To lose the fight is to sacrifice immortality and leave Pai helpless!
name: Final Chapter

description: Captain Britain discovers what lies in the basement of the palace where he grew, and this discover brings to him the menace of a new invicible foe, and the revelation of the truth behind the death of his parents.
name: I Call You Dead
The Revenge Of The Red Skull

description:
Overview

On April 11, 2003, grief turns to hope and resolve when Marvel and its international creative community pay tribute to world's least-heralded heroes - peacemakers. Called simply "411", this special anthology project will tell uplifting stories of people choosing to fight aggression with information and non-violent resistance.

This beautifully illustrated, positive publishing initiative will be filled with true and fictional stories about everyday heroes who are trying to bring peace to their part of the world, featuring the work of contributing artists and writers from Cleveland to Croatia - from Hollywood to Hong Kong.

"411" will also feature diverse contributors from outside the comics industry, including Pulitzer Prize & Tony Award winning playwright Tony Kushner (Angels in America), anti-nuclear activist & Nobel Peace Prize nominee Helen Caldicott (The New Nuclear Danger), and political cartoonist David Rees ("Get Your War On"). A special introduction will be provided by Dr. Arun Gandhi, Mahatma Gandhi's grandson and co-founder of the M. K. Gandhi Institute for Nonviolence.

name: The Night Big Ben Stood Still

description: More inspirational stories of paying tribute to world's least-heralded heroes, peacemakers. Issue #2 of this beautifully illustrated, special anthology tells more uplifting true and fictional stories of everyday people choosing to bring peace to their part of the world by fighting aggression with information and non-violent resistance.
name: The Clarion Call; Enlightenment; Dance!

description: Contains a reprint from Fantastic Four (Vol. 1) #121 (part 2 of 2), entitled: The mysterious mind-blowing secret of Gabriel!
name: ...Gathering of Gladiators!
In the Shadow of the Hawk

description: Contains a reprint from Fantastic Four (Vol. 1) #121 (part 1 of 2), entitled: The mysterious mind-blowing secret of Gabriel!
name: The Fall of the Fourth Reich?

description: Contains material originally published in magazine form as Marvel Superheroes (2nd series) #384-388 and Daredevils #1-11, and The Mighty World of Marvel #7-13
name: Captain Britain

description: Star solves a hostage situation and stops a runaway train, and soon afterwards, rock star Peter Klaptin and his bodyguard Chris Robinson train themselves for combat. After Klaptin witnesses questionable actions on a boat in Lake Michigan, Star flies into action, only to be captured by tiny model airplanes, which attempt to impale him on a radio spire.

As Star saves himself, General Sucarno, a terrorist trying to gain freedom in America, deals with Overlord. Star tries to determine who was behind the runaway train/model airplane incidents, and Chris Robinson is called into action by his former employers, The Vicious Circle, to attack Klaptin. He refuses, but Klaptin and his entire touring crew are attacked during a soundcheck.
